<HTML><HEAD>

<TITLE>FDA Reform - PFF</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/pff/notebook.gif" LINK="#8C1717" VLINK="#545454" ALINK="#FF0000">
<blockquote>
<a href="/pff"><img src="/pff/pffdoc.gif" align="right" border="0"></a>
<P>
<br><br>
<h2>FDA Reform</h2>
</B>
<P>
<CENTER><B>Comments by  Foundation President Jeff Eisenach  on ABC's Nightline</B><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<p>
"The United States is unambiguously still today, thank goodness, the leader in medical technology but that intelligence, that human capital is literally getting on an airplane and flying to Europe and setting up shop and setting up households in Europe.<p><p>

"We simply think the process should be decentralized, that much of the work should be moved out of the hands of government bureaucracies into efficient private sector agencies.  But the same level of safety and efficiency ought to be demanded – both by the private sector companies that are doing the certification and also the FDA and in its final approval.<p><p>

Dr. Eisenach was also quoted in the Wall Street Journal on this subject:  "The FDA, instead of being a 'certifier of products' would become a 'certifier of certifiers,' ensuring that the private entities uphold the agency's standards, he said."  
<p>
